# Cloudflare Pages SPA routing
#
# Cloudflare Pages serves index.html for not-found static routes when no 404.html
# is present, which supports direct visits such as /admin. Keeping the old
# Netlify-style rule `/* /index.html 200` causes current Wrangler/Cloudflare
# validation to report an infinite loop, so no explicit wildcard rewrite is used.
#
# Pages Functions routes such as /functions/auth are handled separately.
